introduction.html.title: Introduction
introduction.html.body:
Introduction
After a  IDE-daemon-client  command is run, the specified command is sent to the host. If the command needs to be run on the host, run it directly on the host. If the command needs to be run on a device, connect the host to the device and run the command on the device.

After Mind Studio is installed, you can log in to the Mind Studio server as the Mind Studio installation user and obtain the IDE-daemon-client tool in the  ~/tools/che/ddk/ddk/uihost/bin  directory.
Alternatively, on the Mind Studio server, you can set environment variables and run a  IDE-daemon-client  command. This document uses this method as an example. You can also log in to the server on the host as the HwHiAiUser user and directly run a  IDE-daemon-client  command. (Currently, the PCIe mode is supported.)

 NOTE:~/tools  is the default  toolpath  setting, which can be customized during Mind Studio installation. You can view the value of  toolpath file in the  scripts/env.conf  file. You can run the  find / -name 'env.conf'  command to view the location of the  env.conf  file in the  script directory.

mind-studio-sends-a-command-to-a-device..title: Mind Studio Sends a Command to a Device
mind-studio-sends-a-command-to-a-device..body:
Mind Studio Sends a Command to a Device
Command Function
Allows Mind Studio to send a command to a device for execution, for example, the command for viewing the date information on the device.
Command Format
IDE-daemon-client --host host_ip_>:port> [--device deviceID>] --cmd command>
Parameter Description
Table  1  Parameter description

Parameter

Description

Mandatory

Default Value



--host

host_ip: Specifies the IP address of the host.port: Specifies the port number.

Yes

The default value of port is 22118.


--device

If the host is connected to multiple devices, you can specify a device using --device deviceID. If the device is not specified, the device with deviceID of 0 is used by default.

No

The default value of deviceID is 0.


--cmd

Specifies the command to be executed on the device. For details about the command list, see Command List.

Yes

-





Example

Log in to the Mind Studio server as the Mind Studio installation user.
Run the following commands to set the environment variables:
export  LD_LIBRARY_PATH=~/tools/che/ddk/ddk/uihost/lib
export  PATH=$PATH:~/tools/che/ddk/ddk/uihost/bin

Run the following command to view the date information on the device:
IDE-daemon-client --host xx.xx.xx.xx:22118 --cmd date

 NOTE:xx.xx.xx.xx  should be replaced with the actual IP address of the host.  



Command List
In commands with variables, variables such as  xxxx  and  yy  should be replaced with the actual directory name and file name, respectively.

Category

Command

Remarks



Command without variables

ide_cmd.sh --reboot

The sudo command is used to improve the user's operation permission. 
The command sent to the device is sudo command, while the actually executed command is reboot mini.

mind-studio-transfers-a-file-to-a-device.title: Mind Studio Transfers a File to a Device
mind-studio-transfers-a-file-to-a-device.body:
Mind Studio Transfers a File to a Device
Command Function
Allows Mind Studio to transfer a file to a device.
Command Format
IDE-daemon-client --host host_ip>:port> [--device deviceID>] --file source_dir> dest_dir>
Parameter Description
Table  1  Parameter description

Parameter

Description

Mandatory

Default Value



--host

host_ip: Specifies the IP address of the host.port: Specifies the port number.

Yes

The default value of port is 22118.


--device

If the host is connected to multiple devices, you can specify a device using --device deviceID. If the device is not specified, the device with deviceID of 0 is used by default.

No

The default value of deviceID is 0.


--file

source_dir: Specifies the directory of the source file on the Mind Studio server, including the file name.dest_dir: Specifies the directory of the destination file on the device, including the file name. dest_dir must be specified. Otherwise, the command fails to be executed. Files can be stored only in the following directories:~/ide_daemon~/HIAI_PROJECTS~/HIAI_DATANDMELSET/opt/mini/var/log/hisi_logs/var/dlog


Yes

-





Example

Log in to the Mind Studio server as the Mind Studio installation user.
Run the following commands to set the environment variables:
export  LD_LIBRARY_PATH=~/tools/che/ddk/ddk/uihost/lib
export  PATH=$PATH:~/tools/che/ddk/ddk/uihost/bin

Run the following command to transfer the A.java file to the device and save the file as B.java:
IDE-daemon-client --host xx.xx.xx.xx:22118 --file /tmp/A.java "~/ide_daemon/B.java"

 NOTE:xx.xx.xx.xx  should be replaced with the actual IP address of the host.

mind-studio-transfers-a-file-to-the-host.title: Mind Studio Transfers a File to the Host
mind-studio-transfers-a-file-to-the-host.body:
Mind Studio Transfers a File to the Host
Command Function
Allows Mind Studio to transfer a file to the host.
Command Format
IDE-daemon-client --host host_ip>:port> --sync source_dir> dest_dir>
Parameter Description
Table  1  Parameter description

Parameter

Description

Mandatory

Default Value



--host

host_ip: Specifies the IP address of the host.port: Specifies the port number.

Yes

The default value of port is 22118.


--sync

source_dir: Specifies the directory of the source file on the Mind Studio server, including the file name.dest_dir: Specifies the directory of the destination file on the host, excluding the file name. For example, the directory of the destination file is ~/ide_daemon or ~/ide_daemon/, both of which indicate that the destination file is stored in the ide_daemon directory. dest_dir must be specified. Otherwise, the command fails to be executed. Files can be stored only in the following directories:~/ide_daemon~/HIAI_PROJECTS~/HIAI_DATANDMELSET/opt/mini/var/log/hisi_logs/var/dlog


Yes

-





Example

Log in to the Mind Studio server as the Mind Studio installation user.
Run the following commands to set the environment variables:
export  LD_LIBRARY_PATH=~/tools/che/ddk/ddk/uihost/lib
export  PATH=$PATH:~/tools/che/ddk/ddk/uihost/bin

Run the following command to transfer the  A.java  file to the specified directory on the host:
IDE-daemon-client --host xx.xx.xx.xx:22118 --sync /tmp/A.java "~/ide_daemon"

 NOTE:xx.xx.xx.xx  should be replaced with the actual IP address of the host.

mind-studio-obtains-a-file-from-the-host.title: Mind Studio Obtains a File from the Host
mind-studio-obtains-a-file-from-the-host.body:
Mind Studio Obtains a File from the Host
Command Function
Allows Mind Studio to obtain a file from the host.
Command Format
IDE-daemon-client --host host_ip>:port> --get dest_dir> source_dir>
Parameter Description
Table  1  Parameter description

Parameter

Description

Mandatory

Default Value



--host

host_ip: Specifies the IP address of the host.port: Specifies the port number.

Yes

The default value of port is 22118.


--get

source_dir: Specifies the directory of the source file on the host, including the file name. Files can be stored only in the following directories:~/ide_daemon~/HIAI_PROJECTS~/HIAI_DATANDMELSET/opt/mini/var/log/hisi_logs/var/dlog
dest_dir: Specifies the directory of the destination file, including the file name. dest_dir must be specified. Otherwise, the command fails to be executed.

Yes

-





Example

Log in to the Mind Studio server as the Mind Studio installation user.
Run the following commands to set the environment variables:
export  LD_LIBRARY_PATH=~/tools/che/ddk/ddk/uihost/lib
export  PATH=$PATH:~/tools/che/ddk/ddk/uihost/bin

Run the following command to obtain the  B.java  file from the host and save it as  A.java:
IDE-daemon-client --host xx.xx.xx.xx:22118 --get /tmp/A.java "~/ide_daemon/B.java"

 NOTE:xx.xx.xx.xx  should be replaced with the actual IP address of the host.

detecting-the-heartbeat-between-mind-stu.title: Detecting the Heartbeat Between Mind Studio and the Host
detecting-the-heartbeat-between-mind-stu.body:
Detecting the Heartbeat Between Mind Studio and the Host
Command Function
Detects the heartbeat between Mind Studio and the host to check whether the server on the host is running.
Command Format
IDE-daemon-client --host host_ip>:port> --detect
Parameter Description
Table  1  Parameter description

Parameter

Description

Mandatory

Default Value



--host

host_ip: Specifies the IP address of the host.port: Specifies the port number.

Yes

The default value of port is 22118.


--detect

Detects the heartbeat. If the heartbeat message is detected, SUCCESS is returned. Otherwise, no information is returned.

Yes

-





Example

Log in to the Mind Studio server as the Mind Studio installation user.
Run the following commands to set the environment variables:
export  LD_LIBRARY_PATH=~/tools/che/ddk/ddk/uihost/lib
export  PATH=$PATH:~/tools/che/ddk/ddk/uihost/bin

Run the following command to check the heartbeat between Mind Studio and the host:
IDE-daemon-client --host xx.xx.xx.xx:22118 --detect

 NOTE:xx.xx.xx.xx  should be replaced with the actual IP address of the host.

setting-the-log-level.html.title: Setting the Log Level
setting-the-log-level.html.body:
Setting the Log Level
Command Function
Sets the log levels for the host and device.
Command Format
IDE-daemon-client --host host_ip>:port> [--device deviceID>] --log 'params>'
Parameter Description
Table  1  Parameter description

Parameter

Description

Mandatory

Default Value



--host

host_ip: Specifies the IP address of the host.port: Specifies the port number.

Yes

The default value of port is 22118.


--device

If the host is connected to multiple devices, you can specify a device using --device deviceID. If the device is not specified, the device with deviceID of 0 is used by default.

No

The default value of deviceID is 0.


--log

params includes the following items:
SetLogLevel sets the global log level. The value 0 indicates the global log level, the value 1 indicates the module-level log level, and the value 2 indicates the event log level. When the event log level is set, enable indicates that the event log level is enabled, and disable indicates that the event log level is disabled.SetLogLevel[moduel:level] sets the log level of a specified module.Level: error, info, warning, or debugmoduleName: dlog, slog, cce...


Yes

-





Example

Log in to the Mind Studio server as the Mind Studio installation user.
Run the following commands to set the environment variables:
export  LD_LIBRARY_PATH=~/tools/che/ddk/ddk/uihost/lib
export  PATH=$PATH:~/tools/che/ddk/ddk/uihost/bin

Run the following commands to set a log level for the host:
IDE-daemon-client --host xx.xx.xx.xx:22118 --log 'SetLogLevel(0)[error]'
IDE-daemon-client --host xx.xx.xx.xx:22118 --log 'SetLogLevel(1)[slog:error]'
IDE-daemon-client --host xx.xx.xx.xx:22118 --log 'SetLogLevel(2)[enable]'

 NOTE:xx.xx.xx.xx  should be replaced with the actual IP address of the host.

mind-studio-sends-information-about-prof.title: Mind Studio Sends Information About Profiling Items to the Host
mind-studio-sends-information-about-prof.body:
Mind Studio Sends Information About Profiling Items to the Host
Command Function
Allows Mind Studio to send the information about profiling items to the host and starts the profiling.
Command Format
IDE-daemon-client --host host_ip>:port> --profile "params>"
Parameter Description
Table  1  Parameter description

Parameter

Description

Mandatory

Default Value



--host

host_ip: Specifies the IP address of the host.port: Specifies the port number.

Yes

The default value of port is 22118.


--profile

Specifies profiling items in params.

Yes

-





Prerequisites
Project files compiled on Mind Studio are copied to the corresponding directories on the host in advance.
For example, if the project name on Mind Studio is  test  and compiled project files are stored in the  /projects/test  directory, copy the  /projects/test  directory and the files in it to the directory (for example,  ~/HIAI_PROJECTS/workspace_mind_studio) on the host.
Example

Log in to the Mind Studio server as the Mind Studio installation user.
Run the following commands to set the environment variables:
export  LD_LIBRARY_PATH=~/tools/che/ddk/ddk/uihost/lib
export  PATH=$PATH:~/tools/che/ddk/ddk/uihost/bin

Run the following command:
IDE-daemon-client --host xx.xx.xx.xx:22118 --profile "{\"ddk_dir\": \"~/tools/che/ddk/ddk\",\"app\": \"main\",\"app_dir\": \"/xxx/xxx\", \"umode\": \"MIND\",\"result_dir\": \"/projects/test/profiling_output\",\"peripheral_profiling\": \"\",\"ts_cpu_profiling\": \"off\",\"ai_cpu_profiling\": \"off\",\"rts_profiling\": \"on\",\"ai_core_profiling_mode\": \"\",\"ai_core_profiling\": \"off\",\"hiai_engine_profiling\": \"off\",\"framework_profiling\": \"off\",\"ctrl_cpu_profiling\": \"off\",\"profiling_mode\": \"online\",\"llc_profiling\": \"off\",\"ddr_profiling\": \"on\"}"

 NOTE:   

Replace  xx.xx.xx.xx  after  --host  with the actual IP address of the host.  
Replace  /xxx/xxx  after  app_dir  with the directory of the app on the host. For example, if the files related to the compiled project on Mind Studio are copied to the  ~/HIAI_PROJECTS/workspace_mind_studio  directory on the host, the app directory is  ~/HIAI_PROJECTS/workspace_mind_studio/project name/user-defined directory.  
Replace  app  with the application name (for example, main) in the directory specified by  app_dir.  
Replace  result_dir  with the actual directory on the Mind Studio server. After running the command, you can view the profiling result in the directory specified by  result_dir.  
For details about how to configure profiling items, see section  Profiling  in the  Ascend 310 Mind Studio Auxiliary Tools.

collecting-dump-information-recorded-by-.title: Collecting Dump Information Recorded by the Black Box on the Host
collecting-dump-information-recorded-by-.body:
Collecting Dump Information Recorded by the Black Box on the Host
Command Function
Collects dump information recorded by the black box on the host.
Command Format
IDE-daemon-client --host host_ip>:port> --bbox params>
Parameter Description
Table  1  Parameter description

Parameter

Description

Mandatory

Default Value



--host

host_ip: Specifies the IP address of the host.port: Specifies the port number.

Yes

The default value of port is 22118.


--bbox

params includes the following items:
--all: Obtains the list and directory of files on all abnormal devices.--status: Obtains the number of exceptions on all devices. If there is only one device, the value, for example, {(0,3)}, is returned, indicating that three exceptions occur on device 0. If there are multiple devices, the value, for example, {(1,3);(0,3)} is returned, indicating that three exceptions occur on device 0 and three exceptions occur on device 1. Information about multiple devices is separated by a semicolon ;.--latest: Obtains the list and directory of the latest files of abnormal devices. If FAILED is returned, no exception occurs.'--filter --device deviceID --except-num n': Obtains the lists and directories of files from the first n abnormal devices among the specified devices. If multiple devices need to be specified, separate them with a comma (,). --filter --device deviceID --except-num n must be placed in single or double quotation marks.

Yes

-





Example

Log in to the Mind Studio server as the Mind Studio installation user.
Run the following commands to set the environment variables:
export  LD_LIBRARY_PATH=~/tools/che/ddk/ddk/uihost/lib
export  PATH=$PATH:~/tools/che/ddk/ddk/uihost/bin

Run the following command to collect the lists and directories of files from all abnormal devices on the host:
IDE-daemon-client --host xx.xx.xx.xx:22118 --bbox --all

 NOTE:xx.xx.xx.xx  should be replaced with the actual IP address of the host.

obtaining-the-information-about-the-devi.title: Obtaining the Information About the Device Connected to the Host
obtaining-the-information-about-the-devi.body:
Obtaining the Information About the Device Connected to the Host
Command Function
Allows Mind Studio to obtain the information about the device connected to the host.
Command Format
IDE-daemon-client --host host_ip>:port> --api params>
Parameter Description
Table  1  Parameter description

Parameter

Description

Mandatory

Default Value



--host

host_ip: Specifies the IP address of the host.port: Specifies the port number.

Yes

The default value of port is 22118.


--api

params includes the following items:
device_info: Indicates the list of devices connected to the host.device_status: Only the status of the camera on the developer board can be queried. The value 0 indicates that the camera does not exist, and the value 1 indicates that the camera exists. If the value 100 is returned, 1 indicates the Hi3559 chip, and the last two 0s indicate that the two cameras do not exist.board_id: Only the device type on the developer board can be queried.sys_version: Only the product version of the developer board can be queried.

Yes

-





Example

Log in to the Mind Studio server as the Mind Studio installation user.
Run the following commands to set the environment variables:
export  LD_LIBRARY_PATH=~/tools/che/ddk/ddk/uihost/lib
export  PATH=$PATH:~/tools/che/ddk/ddk/uihost/bin

Run the following command to obtain the list of all devices connected to the host:
IDE-daemon-client --host xx.xx.xx.xx:22118 --api device_info

 NOTE:xx.xx.xx.xx  should be replaced with the actual IP address of the host.

Parameter

Description

Mandatory

synchronizing-the-time-between-mind-stud.title: Synchronizing the Time Between Mind Studio and the Host
synchronizing-the-time-between-mind-stud.body:
Synchronizing the Time Between Mind Studio and the Host
Command Function
Synchronizes the time of the host server with the time of the Mind Studio server.
Command Format
IDE-daemon-client --host host_ip>:port> --time
Parameter Description
Table  1  Parameter description

Parameter

Description

Mandatory

Default Value



--host

host_ip: Specifies the IP address of the host.port: Specifies the port number.

Yes

The default value of port is 22118.


--time

If only --host and --time are used, the time of the Mind Studio server prevails. That is, the time on the host server is synchronized to be consistent with that of the Mind Studio server.
The IDE-daemon-client commands with the --host parameter can include the --time parameter, which is optional. The following provides an example:
IDE-daemon-client --host host_ip>:port> --detect --time

Yes

-





Example

Log in to the Mind Studio server as the Mind Studio installation user.
Run the following commands to set the environment variables:
export  LD_LIBRARY_PATH=~/tools/che/ddk/ddk/uihost/lib
export  PATH=$PATH:~/tools/che/ddk/ddk/uihost/bin

Run the command to check the heartbeat and synchronize the time:
IDE-daemon-client --host xx.xx.xx.xx:22118 --detect --time

 NOTE:xx.xx.xx.xx  should be replaced with the actual IP address of the host.
